title: For Sale:  SAA COLT SINGLE ACTION ARMY mfg 1893 Conv. to .22lr
postcontent: It's an interesting point that while there are almost always five or six original Colt Richards Mason conversions available on auction sites, and at least as many original 1st generation Colt Dragoons as well, not to mention dozens of 1st generation Single Action Army's, all of which are considered to be 'rare', the vast, vast majority of antique pistol collectors have never seen one of these .22 conversions in real life, or even ever seen one offered for sale. I have been in this for more than fifty years and have seen two. THIS genuinely is RARE, and if you want to plink with a full size genuine Colt SAA, this may be the last one you ever see available. An interesting gun!This is an original COLT SINGLE ACTION ARMY made in 1893. Rebored and rechambered since then to .22 lr. Genuine stag grips. Solid good looking gun. $1185. postcontent: Only ~200 round fired. Very Clean!Comes with one magazine, wallet holster, case, original box and 75 rounds. GREAT FOR ALL-DAY CONCEALED CARRYThe Beretta 3032 Tomcat is tiny. Besides offering the power of the .32 ACP cartridge, it sports a tough and durable blued-steel finish. This double/single-action auto-pistol is perfect for deep concealment or as a backup second handgun.EASY OPERATIONThe controls of the Beretta 3032 Tomcat are designed to be simple and to provide safety and peace of mind while carrying. The two-position safety engages crisply and positively, and locks the slide as well as preventing the pistol from firing. The magazine release is located to the left of the grip, making it easy to locate and operate even with one hand.CONVENIENT TIP-UP BARREL DESIGNIts tip-up barrel design makes it easy to load, operate, and maintain, while its traditional looks give it the allure of a true classic. Thanks to this design, you never need to rack the slide and you can load that first round directly into the chamber. This is especially convenient in cold weather, or for people with weaker hands. Another advantage is that the barrel may be easily cleaned without taking the pistol apart, making it convenient to give the pistol a quick wipe after a session at the range.TIP-UP BARREL RELEASE LATCHThe Beretta 3032 Tomcat‚Äôs barrel tips up (that is, it swings upward pivoting near the muzzle, thereby exposing the chamber); this is achieved by simply operating the tip-up barrel release latch on the side of the pistol.TIP-UP BARRELThe tip-up barrel design has several advantages. It makes it easy to visually check whether the chamber is loaded and it allows for effortless loading and unloading without racking the slide. This last feature makes it particularly ideal for shooters with weaker hands.EASY TO CONCEAL AND SHOOT Right from their inception, Beretta small frame pistols such as the Beretta 3032 Tomcat were designed to be carried concealed. The lines are snag-free, with the sights being engineered to easily slide in and out of a holster, pocket, or belly-band without catching on anything. Thanks to this and other details, the Beretta 3032 Tomcat will feel ergonomic and efficient in your hands, in spite of its diminutive size.BLUED FINISHThe blued steel finish on this handgun makes it highly resistant to sweat, rain, and powder residues.
